        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Aug. 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Hooker,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. so much like to see you, but we start tomorrow morning for Abinger to pay Farrer &amp; Effie a visit of a few days (I have not done such a feat for 25 years) as they have tempted me most kindly by offering me a room to myself. Afterwards we go to William at Southampton &amp; shall not return till 20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> or 21<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> or 22<hi rend="superscript">nd</hi>;<ref target="#foot.f2"/> So that Sunday 24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> is first day possible for you &amp; Gen. Strachey. But I will not hear of a “luncheon”: you must come down to dinner on Saturday &amp; return as early as you like on Monday.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> The common flowers to be named will keep till you come then, or soon afterwards, &amp; if you cannot come at such time, I will most gratefully send them you.—</p>
<p>I am glad to hear so good an account of Huxley.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>Farewell till we meet. | Ever yours | Ch Darwin</p>
<p>I have been half-killing myself over Drosera, which is a never ending job, over which I could spend my life.<ref target="#foot.f5"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.5 hear] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘here’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.6 return] <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> <hi rend="italic">illeg</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.7 common] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
