        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8999.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. D. Hooker, 3 August 1873</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD visited Thomas Henry and Katherine Euphemia (Effie) Farrer from 5 to 9 August 1873; he visited <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1245.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Erasmus Darwin</ref> from 9 to 21 August (see ‘Journal’ (Appendix II)). Because of his frequent bouts of illness, CD rarely visited anyone other than immediate family.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4584.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Richard Strachey</ref> and Hooker visited Down on 23 August 1873 (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> diary (DAR 242)).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">Hooker had accompanied <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2486.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Thomas Henry Huxley</ref> for part of his recuperative visit to France and Germany (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8999.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. D. Hooker, 3 August 1873</ref> and n. 1).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">CD had resumed his experiments on the physiology of <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi> from mid-June (see ‘Journal’ (Appendix II) and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8996.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. V. Carus, 2 August [1873]</ref>).</note>
        </div>        
            
